---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 127
By: Swami Sivananda
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Sacrifice and Suffering=Contemptus Mundi
  - Combat-Action=Metanoia=The Inversion of Values
---
All that one calls honour, name, or reputation must be considered by the
spiritual aspirant as filth or poison, whereas he must accept dishonour and
scorn in the way that one wears a golden necklace. That is how he can reach
the goal with certitude.
